---
import Footer from "../../components/Footer2.astro";
import Link from "../../components/General/Link.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import ProjectCats from "../../components/Project/Project-Cats.astro";
import ToolCard from "../../components/Tool-Card.astro";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

import PhotoSwipeImage from "../../components/General/PhotoSwipeImage.astro";

import modeler from "../../assets/projects/modelFull.png";
import whitespace from "../../assets/projects/model-whitespace.png";
import whitespace2 from "../../assets/projects/model-whitespace2.png";
import builder from "../../assets/projects/builder.png";
---

<Layout title="Hunter Van Lear">
  <Header />
  <main class="container flex flex-col">
    <Link arrowOnLeft text="projects" url="/work" />
    <div class="hero-container">
      <div>
        <section class="container">
          <div class="container-name">
            <h1 class="mt-4 text-sans-bold flex flex-col md:flex-row">
              <p class="primary-header">BPMN Modeler</p>
            </h1>
          </div>
          <div class="container-project-cats flex mt-5">
            <ProjectCats color="#05B4FF" title="UI Design" />
            <ProjectCats color="#05B4FF" title="Product Design" />
            <ProjectCats color="#05B4FF" title="Design Systems" />
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="section-description grid mt-8 mb-20">
          <div class="container-description text-sans">
            <div class="container-description__description">
              <p class="description">
                A comprehensive UI and UX overhaul a web-based canvas tool used
                for modeling and creating complex <span class="text-sans-bold"
                  >B</span
                >usiness <span class="text-sans-bold">P</span>rocess and <span
                  class="text-sans-bold">M</span
                >odel <span class="text-sans-bold">N</span>otation diagrams. The
                aim was to enhance usability, aesthetics, and functionality,
                making the tool more intuitive and efficient for users.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
      <PhotoSwipeImage
        image={{
          src: modeler.src,
          width: 2165,
          height: 1484,
          thumbnail: modeler,
        }}
        alt="Process Modeler Update Screenshot"
      />
    </div>

    <section class="section-goal">
      <div class="container-split-list">
        <div class="container-split-list__left">
          <div class="list-header text-sans-bold">
            <h2 class="secondary-header">Core Problems</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="list-text text-sans">
            <ul class="list">
              <li>
                <span class="text-sans-bold"> Cumbersome User Experience:</span>
                 Users encounter difficulties navigating and operating within
                the canvas space, resulting in a cumbersome and frustrating
                experience.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="text-sans-bold"> Limited Maneuverability:</span>
                 The tool lacks flexibility and ease of movement within the
                canvas, making it challenging for users to efficiently interact
                with and manipulate elements.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="text-sans-bold"> Estate:</span> Poor Usage of
                Screen Real Inefficient allocation of screen space further
                compounds usability issues, hindering users' ability to
                effectively visualize and work with their diagrams.
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="text-sans-bold">Inflexible Menu Structure:</span>
                 The existing menu structure fails to accommodate new features
                easily, leading to delays in implementing enhancements and
                limiting the tool's scalability and adaptability.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="container-split-list__right">
          <div class="list-header text-sans-bold">
            <h2 class="secondary-header">Complications</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="list-text text-sans">
            <ul class="list">
              <li>
                <span class="text-sans-bold"
                  >Tight Development Schedule for a Large Project:</span
                >
                 The project faced a tight development schedule, especially
                considering the magnitude of the redesign effort required.
                Balancing the need for thorough testing and iteration with the
                constraints of the timeline presented a significant challenge
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="text-sans-bold"
                  >Complicated Code Base and Potential Performance Issues:</span
                >
                 The canvas tool operates on a complicated code base, which
                could potentially lead to performance issues and hinder the
                smooth functioning of the tool. Addressing this challenge
                requires careful optimization and refactoring to ensure optimal
                performance and stability.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="lg:mt-20 mb-20">
      <div class="container-challenge">
        <!-- <div class="container-challenge__challenge">
          <div class="challenge-header text-sans-bold">
            <h2 class="secondary-header">Cognitive Load</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="challenge-text text-sans">
            <p>
              The project aims to lower cognitive load for users navigating the
              inherent complexities of BPMN by minimizing visual clutter,
              simplifying the interface, and implementing modern UI design
              paradigms. We intend to enhance user experience through intuitive
              design, logical feature organization, and maximizing canvas
              workspace, thus enabling easier interaction and reducing the
              mental effort required for diagram creation. By adopting
              strategies like modular menus and progressive disclosure, we focus
              on presenting only necessary information, making the tool more
              approachable and efficient, and allowing users to concentrate on
              their modeling tasks without unnecessary distractions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div> -->
        <div class="container-image__two-col">
          <PhotoSwipeImage
            image={{
              src: whitespace.src,
              width: 2128,
              height: 1091,
              thumbnail: whitespace,
            }}
            figcap="Unused white space"
            alt="White space present on old modeler"
          />
          <PhotoSwipeImage
            image={{
              src: whitespace2.src,
              width: 2128,
              height: 1091,
              thumbnail: whitespace2,
            }}
            figcap="Maximizing canvas space through more efficent menu design"
            alt="White space present on old modeler"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <div class="container-__three-col"></div>
    </section>
    <section class="section-challenge">
      <div class="container-challenge-cont">
        <div class="container-challenge-cont__image flex flex-col space-y-20">
          <PhotoSwipeImage
            image={{
              src: builder.src,
              width: 2213,
              height: 1796,
              thumbnail: builder,
            }}
            alt="Process Modeler Design System components"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="container-challenge-cont__challenge">
          <div class="challenge-text text-sans">
            <div class="challenge-header text-sans-bold">
              <h2 class="secondary-header">A Design System</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              The project necessitated the creation of a design system to
              streamline and unify the development process, enhancing
              collaboration between designers and developers. By establishing a
              consistent set of design principles and components, the system
              fostered a cohesive user experience and accelerated the
              design-to-development workflow. Leveraging a design system
              empowered the team to iterate more efficiently, ensuring that
              changes were uniformly applied across the tool, reducing
              redundancy and miscommunication. This cohesive approach not only
              sped up project timelines but also ensured that the tool remained
              scalable and adaptable to future enhancements, making it a
              critical investment for the project's long-term success and
              maintainability.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer id="footer">
    <Footer />
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    min-height: 85vh;
    margin: auto;
    padding: 1rem;
    /* max-width: calc(100% - 2rem); */
    color: var(--clr-white);
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    animation: transitionIn 1s;
  }

  .img_screen {
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .primary-header {
    line-height: 0.8;
    font-size: 5rem;
  }

  .secondary-header {
    font-size: 3rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1000px) {
    .primary-header {
      font-size: 14.06vw;
    }
    .primary-header p:last-child {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .secondary-header {
      font-size: 9vw;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
  }

  .hero-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1000px) {
    .hero-container {
      flex-direction: row;
    }
  }

  .section-description {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(9, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .description {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .container-description {
    display: grid;
    grid-column: 1 / 13;
  }

  .container-project-cats {
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .container-description {
      grid-column: 1 / 10;
    }
  }

  .container-challenge-cont__image {
    order: 2;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .container-challenge-cont__image {
      order: 1;
    }
    .container-challenge-cont__challenge {
      order: 2;
    }
  }

  .list {
    list-style: unset;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  ul.list li {
    padding: 1rem 0;
  }

  .container-split-list,
  .container-challenge-cont {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 30px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1000px) {
    .container-split-list,
    .container-challenge-cont {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  /* .container-split-list__left {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    column-gap: 1rem;
    row-gap: 2rem;
    order: 1;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  } */

  @media (min-width: 1000px) {
    .container-split-list__left {
      order: 0;
      margin: unset;
    }
  }

  .container-challenge {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 30px;
  }

  .container-image__two-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .byline {
    padding: 0.1rem 0;
    animation-delay: 1s;
    animation: transitionLeft 1s;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stagger {
    animation: transitionLeft 1.3s;
  }

  /* ANIMATIONS */

  @keyframes transitionIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(10px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  @keyframes transitionLeft {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateX(-5px);
    }
    80% {
      transform: translateX(3px);
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateX(0);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    #links-section {
      flex-direction: row;
    }
  }
</style>
